*gmp_abs*

(PHP 4 >= 4.0.4, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

gmp_abs â€” Absolute value

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  gmp_abs(GMP|int|string $num): GMP~

Get the absolute value of a number.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num}

  A GMP object, an int, or a string that can be interpreted as a number
  following the same logic as if the string was used in |gmp_init| with
  automatic base detection (i.e. when {base} is equal to 0).

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

Returns the absolute value of {num}, as a GMP number.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 gmp_abs() example

<?php >
  $abs1 = gmp_abs("274982683358");
  $abs2 = gmp_abs("-274982683358");

  echo gmp_strval($abs1) . "\n";
  echo gmp_strval($abs2) . "\n";
<?>

The above example will output:

274982683358
274982683358


